race.comment: ELONIA (8) made debut over the winter on heavy ground and led early but was swamped late and sent for another break. Sharpened with two recent Flemington jump-outs and well worth another try. PRESTIGE ZERPRISE (3) made late ground in a richer maiden on debut and finished sixth. Better for the experience and should be winding up late. IMMORTAL JUSTICE (4) resumes from a long break and for a new yard. Has two minor placings to her name and on best figures should run well here. MISS NAVRATILOVA (11) is a three-year-old filly by Pariah out of Miss Sharapova and a half to Group 2 winner Doubtland. Well educated and stable running hot. Watch the market closely. MAY BE BUBBLES (10) is another first starter. Three-year-old filly by Lonhro out of Tracy May and presents on the back of a Caulfield trial win. Bold run expected.
